==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Freeman
<hw>Free"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Freemen</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[AS.
<ets>fre⟦oacute⟧man</ets>; <ets>fre⟦oacute⟧</ets>free + <ets>mann</ets>
man.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who enjoys liberty, or who is not
subject to the will of another; one not a slave or vassal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A member of a corporation, company, or city,
possessing certain privileges; a member of a borough, town, or State,
who has the right to vote at elections. See <er>Liveryman</er>.</def>
<rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Both having been made <qex>freemen</qex> on the same day.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Free-martin</ent>⟦br⟧
